OL,6,FKaren Smyth, from the Northern Ireland
OL,7,FConsumer Council, said: "While this is
OL,8,Funwelcome news, we are aware the main
OL,9,Fdriver for this is an increase to
OL,10,Fmarket operation and network costs,
OL,11,Funfortunately this is being passed
OL,12,Funto consumers.
OL,14,F"This is the first tariff increase
OL,15,Ffrom the regulated Power NI in two
OL,16,Fyears and the Consumer Council work
OL,17,Fclosely with the Utility Regulator to
OL,18,Fensure consumers are protected and
OL,19,Fsupported, and no unnecessary costs
OL,20,Fare added, or additional profits are
OL,21,Fmade by the supplier.
